\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 I despise you for the manner in which you have taken root in my brain like some parasite and cling to every neuron and fold; I resent you for having been good to me. You may be the worst mistake I\'92ve ever made. I think I wish I had never met you. But I have met you; at points perhaps I had even known you. And so it is of no use to resent what cannot be changed. You exist in my life, arguably for the worse, and I lack the courage to remove you from it.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs32 It appears that I am exhibiting the symptoms of love. Clarity is my standard solution \'97 and writing is already a dangerous act because I have found that in some way every word I write finds its way into your hands. But no matter, and if you\'92re reading this\'97 well, initially I wanted to say something along the lines of 
\f2\i \strokec2 fuck you
\f0\i0 \strokec2 , but I\'92ve decided not to.
\f1\fs24 \
